#: ../../../reference/ufuncs.rst:422
msgid ""
"The Python function ``max()`` will find the maximum over a one-dimensional "
"array, but it will do so using a slower sequence interface. The reduce "
"method of the maximum ufunc is much faster. Also, the ``max()`` method will "
"not give answers you might expect for arrays with greater than one "
"dimension. The reduce method of minimum also allows you to compute a total "
"minimum over an array."
msgstr ""

