#: ../../../reference/ufuncs.rst:432:<autosummary>:1
#: ../../../reference/ufuncs.rst:447:<autosummary>:1
msgid "Element-wise minimum of array elements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/ufuncs.rst:435
msgid ""
"the behavior of ``maximum(a, b)`` is different than that of ``max(a, b)``. "
"As a ufunc, ``maximum(a, b)`` performs an element-by-element comparison of "
"`a` and `b` and chooses each element of the result according to which "
"element in the two arrays is larger. In contrast, ``max(a, b)`` treats the "
"objects `a` and `b` as a whole, looks at the (total) truth value of ``a > "
"b`` and uses it to return either `a` or `b` (as a whole). A similar "
"difference exists between ``minimum(a, b)`` and ``min(a, b)``."
msgstr ""

